The paper deals with algorithms in the congested clique model, which is a model of distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents algorithms for graph-theoretic problems, such as all-pairs shortest paths, diameter, maximum matching, and minimum vertex cover, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also uses algebraic techniques, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
